945
01:39:16,758 --> 01:39:19,175
<i>But you were too much.</i>

946
01:39:19,258 --> 01:39:21,842
<i>You would ask,
"How much do you love me?"</i>

947
01:39:22,133 --> 01:39:24,592
<i>You were hungry for love,
my poor Rosalia.</i>

948
01:39:24,883 --> 01:39:27,800
<i>Too hungry.</i>

949
01:39:29,883 --> 01:39:31,550
ONE LAW FOR ALL

950
01:39:31,842 --> 01:39:36,342
<i>There's not much to say about the trial.
It went much as I expected.</i>

951
01:39:36,883 --> 01:39:38,467
Gentlemen of the jury...

952
01:39:42,925 --> 01:39:46,717
<i>The attorney, De Marzi, was brilliant,
impassioned and sarcastic.</i>

953
01:39:46,800 --> 01:39:48,092
<i>Moving and moved.</i>

954
01:39:48,217 --> 01:39:52,633
<i>He played the entire scale of emotions
with confident precision.</i>

955
01:39:52,883 --> 01:39:55,258
<i>He didn't go so far as to 
mention the Crusades,</i>

956
01:39:55,425 --> 01:39:58,300
<i>but he did cite Othello
and our countryman Turiddu.</i>

957
01:39:58,717 --> 01:39:59,925
<i>Mama was there.</i>

958
01:40:00,050 --> 01:40:02,717
<i>Crying, the poor soul.</i>

959
01:40:02,842 --> 01:40:06,633
<i>Yes, even I was close to tears.</i>

960
01:40:06,717 --> 01:40:08,550
<i>Then he brought my father into it:</i>

961
01:40:08,717 --> 01:40:10,758
<i>A debauched corrupter of innocents,</i>

962
01:40:10,883 --> 01:40:13,925
<i>undoubtedly infected with some 
unmentionable disease,</i>

963
01:40:14,050 --> 01:40:16,008
<i>producer of debts and bastards galore.</i>

964
01:40:16,092 --> 01:40:18,133
<i>Clearly, grave hereditary dysfunction</i>

965
01:40:18,217 --> 01:40:20,925
<i>could be added to my wounded honor.</i>

966
01:40:21,050 --> 01:40:23,258
<i>Finally, he produced the widow Patanè.</i>

967
01:40:23,550 --> 01:40:26,175
<i>He couldn't produce her children,
as they were still very young.</i>

968
01:40:26,300 --> 01:40:28,467
<i>And the penal code forbade it.</i>

969
01:40:28,550 --> 01:40:30,133
<i>But he showed us their pictures.</i>

970
01:40:30,217 --> 01:40:33,675
<i>The image of those poor orphans
helped my case to no end.</i>

971
01:40:33,800 --> 01:40:35,342
<i>I don't really know why.</i>

972
01:40:35,425 --> 01:40:37,508
<i>Perhaps because in Italy, children...</i>

973
01:40:38,217 --> 01:40:40,092
<i>Well, children will always be children.</i>

974
01:40:41,092 --> 01:40:43,258
Silence! His Honor is entering 
the courtroom.

975
01:40:53,925 --> 01:40:55,717
In the name of the Italian people...

976
01:40:57,050 --> 01:40:59,342
<i>Three years. The minimum.</i>

977
01:40:59,592 --> 01:41:03,175
<i>Actually, a little less than the minimum.
I received a small pardon.</i>

978
01:41:03,258 --> 01:41:06,550
<i>I won't say I'd predicted it,
but I was sort of counting on it.</i>

979
01:41:06,758 --> 01:41:10,217
<i>On average there's a pardon
every three years, so it was my due.</i>

980
01:41:11,092 --> 01:41:15,592
<i>I can't say it was a pleasant three years,
but it's behind me now.</i>

981
01:41:22,800 --> 01:41:25,842
<i>I was suddenly seized by a strange fear.</i>

982
01:41:27,050 --> 01:41:30,133
- Waiter, take care of the bill.
- Thank you, sir.

983
01:41:32,758 --> 01:41:35,717
<i>During those months
I'd received letters from Angela.</i>

984
01:41:35,800 --> 01:41:38,342
<i>But only a few.
And they were rather vague.</i>

985
01:41:38,467 --> 01:41:42,092
<i>She always said she prayed for me
and made constant vows.</i>

986
01:41:42,217 --> 01:41:46,050
<i>Perhaps it was the natural shyness
of our southern women.</i>

987
01:41:46,508 --> 01:41:47,717
<i>Or perhaps...</i>

988
01:41:47,925 --> 01:41:50,842
<i>No, it couldn't be.
That would be too unfair.</i>

989
01:41:56,967 --> 01:41:58,508
He's here!

990
01:42:02,050 --> 01:42:03,675
He's here!

991
01:42:25,550 --> 01:42:27,925
My beloved son!

992
01:43:26,383 --> 01:43:29,717
A FEW MONTHS LATER

993
01:44:05,092 --> 01:44:08,883
<i>Yes, life begins at 40.</i>

994
01:44:09,383 --> 01:44:11,300
<i>It really is true.</i>

